<PageTitle>Section 1: Creation of School Discipline Committee</PageTitle>

<div class="discipline-content">
    <div class="content-header">
        <h1>Section 1: Creation of School Discipline Committee</h1>
        <p class="section-subtitle">DepEd School Discipline Rules of Procedure</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-body">
        <div class="section-card">
            <h2>1.1 Establishment of School Discipline Committee</h2>
            <p>Every public elementary and secondary school shall establish a School Discipline Committee (SDC) to ensure the proper implementation of disciplinary measures and procedures in accordance with DepEd policies and guidelines.</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Purpose</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>To maintain order and discipline in the school</li>
                    <li>To ensure fair and consistent application of disciplinary measures</li>
                    <li>To protect the rights of both students and school personnel</li>
                    <li>To promote a positive learning environment</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>1.2 Legal Basis</h2>
            <p>The creation of the School Discipline Committee is based on:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Republic Act No. 9155 (Governance of Basic Education Act of 2001)</li>
                <li>DepEd Order No. 40, s. 2012 (Child Protection Policy)</li>
                <li>DepEd Order No. 8, s. 2015 (Policy Guidelines on Classroom Assessment)</li>
                <li>Republic Act No. 10627 (Anti-Bullying Act of 2013)</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>1.3 Scope of Authority</h2>
            <p>The School Discipline Committee has the authority to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Investigate disciplinary cases involving students</li>
                <li>Recommend appropriate disciplinary measures</li>
                <li>Ensure due process in disciplinary proceedings</li>
                <li>Monitor compliance with school rules and regulations</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Important Note</h3>
                <p>The School Discipline Committee shall operate within the framework of child protection policies and shall always consider the best interests of the child in all disciplinary proceedings.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

